quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  8,1,"They ask you about the spoils of war. Say, \"They belong to God and His Messenger. So fear God, and set things right among yourselves, and obey God and His Messenger, if you are true believers"
  8,2,"true believers are those whose hearts tremble with awe at the mention of God, and whose faith grows stronger as they listen to His revelations. They are those who put their trust in their Lord"
  8,3,who pray regularly and give in alms out of what We have provided for them
  8,4,"Such are the true believers. They have a high standing with their Lord, His forgiveness and an honourable provision made for them"
  8,5,"As it was your Lord who rightfully brought you forth from your house, even though some of the believers disliked it"
  8,6,"and they disputed with you concerning the truth after it had become manifest, as though they were being driven to their death with open eyes"
  8,7,"God promised you that one of the two parties would fall to you, and you wished that the one without sting should be yours, but God wanted to establish the truth by His words and cut off the root of those who denied the truth"
  8,8,"so that He might prove the truth to be true and the false to be false, however much the wrongdoers might dislike it"